  body
    #main_container.mainContainer
      #row1.imgCarousel
        #top_img.topImg <img src="img/head_img.gif" height="100%" width="100%">
        #top_car.topCar
          ul
            li
              p I have this nagging perception that the web is becoming more commoditized  every day.
              p I believe in the open source hardware movement, and wan't to get involved.
            li 
              p I go to a job interview at Makerbot.
            li 
              p I blow the tech screen (can&apos;t explain closures, can&apos;t build custom events on the fly, without checking the internet, I can&apos;t tell how many subway stations there are in Manhattan)
            li 
              p I look to focus this disappointment into something positive.
              p I know the web stack, I know how to build stuff.
            li
              p I learn all I can about Arduino, I get better at Javascript.
              p I buy a bunch of electronic goodies from makershed.com.
            li
              p I build a toy robot for my son for his 4th birthday.
      .clearfix
      hr
      p Flippy The Robot
      hr
      table#row1.descImg
        tr
          td.rowdesc
            p Flippy is a toy robot  physically built on the Arduino platform and programmed with the modern webstack for its control surface.
          td.rowimg <img src="img/flippy_img1.jpg" height="100%" width="100%">
      hr
      table#row2.imgDesc
        tr
          td.rowimg <img src="img/flippy_img2.jpg" height="100%" width="100%">
          td.rowdesc
            p Flippy was built as a project to introduce my son to electronics and robotics.
      hr
      table#row3.descImg
        tr
          td.rowdesc
            p Flippy's is physically based on the Arduino open source hardware platform.
          td.rowimg <img src="img/flippy_img3.jpg" height="100%" width="100%">
      hr
      table#row4.imgDesc
        tr
          td.rowimg <img src="img/flippy_img4.jpg" height="100%" width="100%">
          td.rowdesc
            p What's really cool is that Flippy's control surface is programmed using HTML, CSS & Javascript.
      hr
      table#row5.descImg
        tr
          td.rowdesc
            p Flippy receives instructions via Breakout.js. If you have a computer, a modern web browser and an active network connection, you can control Flippy.
          td.rowimg <img src="img/flippy_img5.png" height="100%" width="100%">
      hr
      table#row6.imgDesc
        tr
          td.rowimg <iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/OFdzrCj10w0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
          td.rowdesc
            p Here's a video of my son's reaction to Flippy on his birthday.
